Besides, why did the culprit stop part way?

262
00:13:34,651 --> 00:13:36,051
Part way?

263
00:13:36,051 --> 00:13:39,451
Look! There's a hole near the corpse.

264
00:13:39,451 --> 00:13:42,651
I think the culprit was planning to stand her corpse.

265
00:13:42,651 --> 00:13:43,751
True.

266
00:13:43,751 --> 00:13:48,451
If it's the same culprit who killed Ms. Shimizu six months ago,

267
00:13:48,451 --> 00:13:51,951
the culprit might've done it to drain her blood.

268
00:13:51,951 --> 00:13:53,751
The strange bruise on the right upper arm

269
00:13:53,751 --> 00:13:57,051
of the corpse bothers me too.

270
00:13:57,051 --> 00:13:58,551
The thing that bothers me most though

271
00:13:58,551 --> 00:14:02,751
is that the fingertips of both her hands are wounded badly.

272
00:14:02,751 --> 00:14:05,851
True. It doesn't look like something that was incurred

273
00:14:05,851 --> 00:14:08,151
when she tried to fight the culprit off either.

274
00:14:12,051 --> 00:14:14,251
Kamiyo...

275
00:14:14,251 --> 00:14:17,451
Was found killed in the forest?

276
00:14:17,451 --> 00:14:19,551
Was it really Honey?

277
00:14:19,551 --> 00:14:20,851
Yeah.

278
00:14:20,851 --> 00:14:24,451
Oh, no. Why?

279
00:14:24,451 --> 00:14:27,351
More than that, who's the culprit?

280
00:14:27,351 --> 00:14:29,151
The gate guards should've witnessed somebody, right?

281
00:14:29,151 --> 00:14:31,851
They say that after Inspector Otaki left by car,

282
00:14:31,851 --> 00:14:34,651
no one went in or out of the gate.

283
00:14:34,651 --> 00:14:35,951
Nobody did?

284
00:14:35,951 --> 00:14:37,251
It can't be.

285
00:14:37,251 --> 00:14:39,451
Maybe there are other hidden corridors or something

286
00:14:39,451 --> 00:14:42,051
and the culprit could've gone out of the gate from there?

287
00:14:42,051 --> 00:14:45,051
I looked once around the fences of the mansion,

288
00:14:45,051 --> 00:14:47,651
but there was nowhere that you could go out from.

289
00:14:47,651 --> 00:14:50,751
The gate guards said that there are sensors on top of the fence

290
00:14:50,751 --> 00:14:55,151
and if someone were to go over it, they would be caught right away.

291
00:14:55,151 --> 00:14:58,551
Then, maybe from a tunnel or something from the mansion?

292
00:14:58,551 --> 00:15:02,851
The owner made renovations on the mansion in just a week.

293
00:15:02,851 --> 00:15:06,951
There's no way that a tunnel can be dug in such a short time.

294
00:15:06,951 --> 00:15:08,551
That's ridiculous?

295
00:15:08,551 --> 00:15:11,651
Then how did the culprit make it out of the gate?

296
00:15:11,651 --> 00:15:13,551
Moreover, take Kamiyo along?

297
00:15:13,551 --> 00:15:15,551
They flew.

298
00:15:15,551 --> 00:15:21,251
Hakuya who turned into a vampire with those abhorrent wings.

299
00:15:22,451 --> 00:15:23,951
Cool head, Ruri.

300
00:15:23,951 --> 00:15:26,051
This young police detective said that

301
00:15:26,051 --> 00:15:28,251
there're no such things as vampires, didn't he?

302
00:15:28,251 --> 00:15:30,351
Police detective? No, wrong.

303
00:15:30,351 --> 00:15:34,051
I'm Heiji Hattori! A high school detective from Osaka!

304
00:15:34,051 --> 00:15:35,651
A detective?

305
00:15:35,651 --> 00:15:38,251
I thought you were too young to be a police detective.

306
00:15:38,251 --> 00:15:40,351
You're only a high school kid?

307
00:15:40,351 --> 00:15:42,651
Well, I'm going to check things a bit more,

308
00:15:42,651 --> 00:15:45,351
so will you all wait in the dining room again?

309
00:15:45,351 --> 00:15:47,751
-Hey. -You've gotta be kidding!

310
00:15:47,751 --> 00:15:50,051
I was listening to you because I thought you were an officer but...

311
00:15:50,051 --> 00:15:52,851
Honey was killed after all too!

312
00:15:52,851 --> 00:15:56,251
I'll protect myself on my own.

313
00:15:56,251 --> 00:15:58,251
Everyone... Hey, hold it!

314
00:15:58,251 --> 00:16:01,951
Oh. So you're not a police officer.

315
00:16:01,951 --> 00:16:05,751
But if you're a detective, are you training under Mr. Mouri?

316
00:16:05,751 --> 00:16:09,851
Huh? Why should I train under that goofy?

317
00:16:12,351 --> 00:16:13,951
That's right!

318
00:16:13,951 --> 00:16:15,951
I'm supposed to be getting a certificate of proficiency

319
00:16:15,951 --> 00:16:17,651
from my trainer Mouri soon.

320
00:16:18,851 --> 00:16:20,451
Then, can you figure out

321
00:16:20,451 --> 00:16:23,751
the trick of how the owner swung his body around?

322
00:16:23,751 --> 00:16:24,851
Swung?

323
00:16:24,851 --> 00:16:27,951
Remember, the time when the owner stuck his head out

324
00:16:27,951 --> 00:16:31,651
from the window of the dining room hanging.

325
00:16:31,651 --> 00:16:34,051
But, before the curtains were opened,

326
00:16:34,051 --> 00:16:35,351
the owner's silhouette that was lit up

327
00:16:35,351 --> 00:16:36,851
the flash of lightning came from below

328
00:16:36,851 --> 00:16:39,051
and wasn't upside.

329
00:16:39,051 --> 00:16:42,851
Moreover, his body seemed to be like that of a ghost!

330
00:16:47,751 --> 00:16:49,051
If I remember correctly, it was here, wasn't it?

331
00:16:49,051 --> 00:16:50,751
The place where the owner's neck was seen through the window.

332
00:16:50,751 --> 00:16:51,951
Yeah.

333
00:16:55,951 --> 00:16:57,651
How about it, Kudo?

334
00:16:57,651 --> 00:16:59,551
Just as we figured!

335
00:16:59,551 --> 00:17:02,151
Which means that the thing in question...

336
00:17:08,951 --> 00:17:11,251
Great idea.

337
00:17:11,251 --> 00:17:14,751
But this large-scale trick...

338
00:17:14,751 --> 00:17:16,551
Isn't something that can be done right after

339
00:17:16,551 --> 00:17:18,451
coming to his mansion.

340
00:17:18,451 --> 00:17:22,151
Uh, the foursome, do they come to this mansion often?

341
00:17:22,151 --> 00:17:28,551
They were here when I was a child and my mother brought me here.

342
00:17:28,551 --> 00:17:31,551
But after becoming a maid, it's the first time I've met them.

343
00:17:31,551 --> 00:17:35,851
It's been a year since they've all been here.

344
00:17:35,851 --> 00:17:38,551
Everyone asks about how Hakuya is doing

345
00:17:38,551 --> 00:17:41,851
or about his health on the phone.

346
00:17:41,851 --> 00:17:44,751
But they rarely come here.

347
00:17:44,751 --> 00:17:49,251
That's why I thought that somebody among them was "pregnant"

348
00:17:49,251 --> 00:17:53,151
and gathered here to celebrate.

349
00:17:53,151 --> 00:17:54,651
Pregnant?

350
00:17:54,651 --> 00:17:59,051
Because the owner was buying a pool for children

351
00:17:59,051 --> 00:18:01,551
and toy planes by internet shopping

352
00:18:01,551 --> 00:18:05,151
which I thought were gifts for the coming baby!

353
00:18:05,151 --> 00:18:06,451
Before I became a maid here,

354
00:18:06,451 --> 00:18:09,651
he used to often buy me clothes and such, too.

355
00:18:09,651 --> 00:18:13,051
Is that airplane one that flaps its wings and flies?

356
00:18:13,051 --> 00:18:16,351
Yes, it was written so on the invoice.

357
00:18:16,351 --> 00:18:21,151
I thought the box was quite large to be a child's toy.

358
00:18:21,151 --> 00:18:24,851
But, when I asked Kamiyo who came with Mr. Hagawa,

359
00:18:24,851 --> 00:18:27,451
whether she was pregnant,

360
00:18:27,451 --> 00:18:30,751
they said, "No, no way" while laughing.

361
00:18:30,751 --> 00:18:35,551
Then, Kishiharu who came later, was holding a big bag,

362
00:18:35,551 --> 00:18:38,751
so I thought that maybe he had brought a gift.

363
00:18:38,751 --> 00:18:40,751
But, he told me that he had his camera

364
00:18:40,751 --> 00:18:42,551
and tools for developing films inside.

365
00:18:42,551 --> 00:18:44,951
I also asked Mr. and Mrs. Asanobu Torakura

366
00:18:44,951 --> 00:18:47,651
who came a bit earlier than you did, about it,

367
00:18:47,651 --> 00:18:49,051
And Ruri remarked,

368
00:18:49,051 --> 00:18:52,351
"I wonder if Mina and Mr. Hagawa got back together again?"

369
00:18:52,351 --> 00:18:54,651
Then, did you ask everybody else too?

370
00:18:54,651 --> 00:18:58,751
Yes, because they came a bit later than you did.

371
00:18:58,751 --> 00:19:00,851
I was given the cold shoulder, though.

372
00:19:00,851 --> 00:19:02,851
Get back together again? Does that mean that...

373
00:19:02,851 --> 00:19:05,551
Mina and Mr. Hagawa were going with each other?

374
00:19:05,551 --> 00:19:08,551
Yes. But, it seems that passionate Mina

375
00:19:08,551 --> 00:19:12,551
came on too strong for Mr. Hawgawa.

376
00:19:12,551 --> 00:19:15,151
And, before we knew it, Mr. Hagawa had changed partners to Kamiyo.

377
00:19:15,151 --> 00:19:17,951
Then, what about Kishiharu and Ruri?

378
00:19:17,951 --> 00:19:21,951
Those two were engaged to begin with

379
00:19:21,951 --> 00:19:24,751
but after Yoko passed away because of the accident,

380
00:19:24,751 --> 00:19:27,251
Kishiharu became deeply depressed

381
00:19:27,251 --> 00:19:29,451
and called off the engagement.

382
00:19:29,451 --> 00:19:34,051
Then, Asanobu proposed to Ruri and they got married.

383
00:19:34,051 --> 00:19:35,751
It seems that Kishiharu

384
00:19:35,751 --> 00:19:42,451
really liked Yoko who was the owner's fiance.

385
00:19:42,451 --> 00:19:44,251
On the day of Yoko's funeral,

386
00:19:44,251 --> 00:19:46,851
he was crying more than the owner.

387
00:19:46,851 --> 00:19:50,051
But, I heard the maids say that

388
00:19:50,051 --> 00:19:52,351
you were crying a lot too, Mr. Koga.

389
00:19:52,351 --> 00:19:55,051
They say it was probably because you got along very well with her.

390
00:19:55,051 --> 00:19:57,051
No.

391
00:19:57,051 --> 00:19:59,051
Things sort of seem so messed up.

392
00:19:59,051 --> 00:20:03,251
Yeah. Everyone seems to have a motive.

393
00:20:05,351 --> 00:20:08,351
Oh, it's text mail from Kishiharu.

394
00:20:08,351 --> 00:20:11,351
He wants me to bring sake up to his room.

395
00:20:11,351 --> 00:20:14,351
Does he know your mail address?

396
00:20:14,351 --> 00:20:16,651
Not only does Kishiharu know!

397
00:20:16,651 --> 00:20:18,551
On the day before they came here,

398
00:20:18,551 --> 00:20:20,151
I sent everyone text mail

399
00:20:20,151 --> 00:20:22,051
that we'd be waiting for them to arrive.

400
00:20:22,051 --> 00:20:23,951
Why go out of your way to do so?

401
00:20:23,951 --> 00:20:24,951
Because the other day,

402
00:20:24,951 --> 00:20:29,151
the owner gave me everyone's mail address so...

403
00:20:29,151 --> 00:20:31,151
I thought he meant for me to greet all

404
00:20:31,151 --> 00:20:35,051
who were coming beforehand, so I sent out the text mail.

405
00:20:35,051 --> 00:20:38,051
I often exchange text mail with the owner, you see.

406
00:20:38,051 --> 00:20:41,751
Then, when he told you to come to the European room also...

407
00:20:41,751 --> 00:20:44,051
Yes. I got texted!

408
00:20:44,051 --> 00:20:45,851
-See! -After breakfast,

409
00:20:45,851 --> 00:20:48,651
come to the European room, without telling anyone about it.

410
00:20:48,651 --> 00:20:51,851
Make sure that the butler doesn't see you coming.

411
00:20:51,851 --> 00:20:55,251
But, I saw this mail after noon,

412
00:20:55,251 --> 00:20:59,351
so, I ended up standing him up.

413
00:20:59,351 --> 00:21:01,451
You didn't notice the mail?

414
00:21:01,451 --> 00:21:03,451
I had completely forgotten that

415
00:21:03,451 --> 00:21:06,451
I was charging my cell phone in the bathroom.

416
00:21:06,451 --> 00:21:08,851
It's from Kishiharu, asking me to come ASAP!

417
00:21:08,851 --> 00:21:10,451
I've got to go!

418
00:21:10,751 --> 00:21:13,051
From the text mail...

419
00:21:13,051 --> 00:21:17,851
It doesn't sound like the owner doesn't like her at all.

420
00:21:17,851 --> 00:21:21,451
No joke, you mean nobody's coming to eat the pot sticks?

421
00:21:21,451 --> 00:21:22,851
Have they all gone to sleep?

422
00:21:22,851 --> 00:21:26,951
No. I think that everyone is up

423
00:21:26,951 --> 00:21:29,251
but doesn't feel up to eating.

424
00:21:29,251 --> 00:21:32,751
I think it's best that both of you hurry and get to bed.

425
00:21:32,751 --> 00:21:36,651
Oh, no. When the pot sticks came out so deliciously...

426
00:21:36,651 --> 00:21:40,451
But we ate most of it already.

427
00:21:40,451 --> 00:21:42,151
True.

428
00:21:42,151 --> 00:21:44,851
What shall we do if Conan and Heiji come to eat some?

429
00:21:44,851 --> 00:21:49,051
We've got more ingredients, so we could just make more, right?

430
00:21:51,551 --> 00:21:54,051
I'm sure the culprit is that person.

431
00:21:54,051 --> 00:21:55,551
Right, Kudo?

432
00:21:55,551 --> 00:21:58,851
Yeah. But we have no proof.

433
00:21:58,851 --> 00:22:00,151
Besides...

434
00:22:00,151 --> 00:22:03,551
The way that Kamiyo was killed.

435
00:22:03,551 --> 00:22:07,051
Unless we can figure out that trick, our hands are tied.

436
00:22:07,051 --> 00:22:10,451
How did that person go pass the gate

437
00:22:10,451 --> 00:22:13,351
and kill Kamiyo in the forest?

438
00:23:37,851 --> 00:23:40,351
I hope my daughter's okay?

439
00:23:48,351 --> 00:23:50,951
Now we know for sure

440
00:23:50,951 --> 00:23:55,851
that we're not dealing with a vampire with wings.

441
00:23:55,851 --> 00:23:59,351
Yeah. It's an evil creature all right.

442
00:23:59,351 --> 00:24:02,051
But it's a murderer rather than a vampire!

